item.title: Siberian
item.description: The Siberian is a landrace variety of domestic cat, present in Russia for centuries.

item.title: Somali
item.description: The Somali cat is often described as a long-haired African cat.

item.title: Birman
item.description: The Birman, also called the "Sacred Cat of Burma", is a domestic cat breed.

item.title: Ragdoll
item.description: The Ragdoll is a cat breed with a color point coat and blue eyes. They are large and muscular semi-longhair cat with a soft and silky coat.

item.title: Norwegian Forest Cat
item.description: The Norwegian Forest cat (Norwegian: Norsk skogkatt or Norsk skaukatt) is a breed of domestic cat originating in Northern Europe.

item.title: Chartreux
item.description: The Chartreux is a rare breed of domestic cat from France and is recognised by a number of registries around the world.

item.title: Bengal
item.description: The Bengal cat is a domesticated cat breed created from hybrids of domestic cats, the Asian leopard cat.

item.title: Turkish Van
item.description: The Turkish Van is a semi-long-haired breed of domestic cat, which was developed in the United Kingdom from a selection of cats.

item.title: Ocicat
item.description: The Ocicat is an all-domestic breed of cat which resembles a wild cat but has no recent wild DNA in its gene pool.

item.title: British Shorthair
item.description: The British Shorthair is the pedigreed version of the traditional British domestic cat, with a distinctively chunky body, dense coat and broad face.

item.title: Maine Coon
item.description: The Maine Coon is the largest domesticated cat breed.
